1.
The owner entered into a written contract with either an original contractor or a real
estate developer;
2.
The original contractor was properly licensed or exempt from licensure under Title
58, Chapter 55, Utah Construction Trades Licensing Act; and
3.
The owner paid, in full, the original contractor or real estate developer, or their
successor or assign, in accordance with the written contract and any written or oral
amendments to the contract.
